						<summary>

						<p>On a slab which forms a roof of the Ponni-Amman temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">M.K. Rājakēsarivarman (Sundarachōḷa) Year 5: 962 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Āchchan Veṇṇāyi Naṅgai, of Eṟupāḍi in Kiḻār-kūṟṟam, the wife of Vīravaḷañjiyaṉ of Maṟiyāḍi in Pulivala-nāḍu, had caused the construction of the temple for Piḍāri (Bhaṭṭāraki).</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.</hi> Vol. IV. p. 331.</p>						

						</summary>
